This is a sixty-three year old Vietnam Veteran with a history of TBI following a car accident. The patient reports frequent auditory hallucinations and olfatory hallucinations without paranoid content or delusions. These hallucinations are reported after the TBI episode. In addition, the patient presents with objectively measured deficits in short term memory and other memory-related domains without any significant deficits in instrumental activities of daily living. The subject is fully functional both in his profession and socially. Given the objective measure of memory deficits without meaningful impairment in activities, the subject is being diagnosed as MCI.
